File: Police have arrested 42 illegal immigrants for trying to enter the country illegally. FICKSBURG - Forty-two illegal immigrants are behind bars for trying to enter the country illegally. Police in the Free State says they were caught trying to cross the Caledon River in Ficksburg by using a tube. READ: Home Affairs to deploy more personnel to border posts The group is believed to have come from Lesotho. They will appear in the Ficksburg magistrate's court soon.